      • finalDestination

        public static List<String> finalDestination(List<String> elements)
        Calculates the final destination of a file. This is the parent of any __magic element, and the filename of the path. That is: all intermediate child path elements are discarded. Why so? paths under the magic path include job attempt and task attempt subdirectories, which need to be skipped. If there is a __base directory in the children, then it becomes a base for unflattened paths, that is: all its children are pulled into the final destination.
        Parameters:
        elements - element list.
        Returns:
        the path
